======================================================================
THE COMPUTATIONAL DISCOVERY COMPARISON
======================================================================

Our hypothesis was that LSTM would benefit more from temporal
mechanistic features than XGBoost does. The relevant comparison is
between the NO_TEMPORAL and NO_STATIC_MECH degradation values.

XGBoost:
   Removing temporal features:  -0.12% ±  0.00%
   Removing static features:    +1.58% ±  0.00%
   Algorithm relies MORE on static features (diff: 1.70 pp)

LSTM:
   Removing temporal features:  -4.60% ±  7.39%
   Removing static features:    -4.70% ±  7.44%
   Algorithm relies MORE on temporal features (diff: 0.10 pp)

